SECDR13C (SecureDrive V1.3c Edgar Swank
<edgar@spectrx.saigon.com>, enhancing 1.0 by Mike Ingle
<mikeingle@delphi.com>) is a 2.4k TSR that will encrypt up to 4 partitions
(or 2 floppies) using the very secure IDEA conventional encryption method (as
in PGP 2.0), allowing free access to the encrypted information by
applications and prompting for a password the first time the partition or
disk is accessed. Enhancement and bugfix. Freeware; GNU Copyleft. Source in
Turbo C++
